reviews.text:
Mugi Tamago is a food stall hidden inside Yata, a Japanese supermarket in APM. I missed it the first time, and found it after walking around Yata for the second time.

Mugi Tamago is famous for their tamagoyaki, Japanese egg roll omelette, as well as barley rice. They seem to be a nice and healthy combination for dinner. There are also quite a lot of seemingly healthy bentos and snacks option in their fridge, which appeared to be more money worthy than the set I ordered… I was kinda hungry and directly placed an order for a tamagoyaki dinner set without taking a look at the fridge…Lesson learnt.

For HKD$82, this set is a bit overpriced. There were only 3 little pieces of deep fried chicken, which were cold and soggy. There was even a thick layer of oil on top of the dipping sauce…

For the German Potato tamagoyaki (available in APM only but not the Shatin branch), there were quite a lot of potato inside, but only a few bacon pieces at the other end of the omelette. The whole tamagoyaki was quite oily indeed, I guess the chef lacks the skills to make a good one and needs quite a bit of help from oil.

The miso soup was ordinary, and the barley rice was surprisingly nice. I guess the best part of the set is actually this barley rice…Hum…I guess I would go for the bento boxes or stuff in the fridge next time.
Taste good!!! Affordable and hot enough~
Japanese egg omelette available here, it was hot enough
一田food court裡面的小店。食材還是很用心的，的確是日本麥米和日本蛋，豆腐漢堡也不錯，外面一層薄脆的～蛋卷口感也是軟綿綿的，不會煮得死硬。在大商場，這個食材，售這個價格，不算貴了。
這個咖喱宗田鰹魚湯烏冬，認真一般，只有鹹味沒有咖喱味，玉子蛋尚算OK！有兩件八爪魚，硬度𡁻吾到！
